olive oil
2 potato
1 beetroot
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
½ carrot
1 cucumber
1 bag herbs
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet falafel mix
1 packet Currants
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 packet Apricot Sauce
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Garlic Dip

Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks. Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with chermoula spice blend and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Meanwhile, grate carrot (see ingredients). Thinly
slice cucumber into rounds. Pick and thinly slice
herbs. Roughly chop roasted almonds.

In a medium bowl, combine carrot, falafel mix,
currants, fine breadcrumbs and a pinch of
salt. Using damp hands, roll and press heaped
tablespoons of falafel mixture into small balls (3
falafels per person). Transfer to a plate.

In a large frying pan, heat olive oil (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people) over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, cook falafels, turning, until browned and heated through, 5-7 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Remove pan from heat, then add apricot sauce and toss falafels to coat.

In a second medium bowl, combine mixed leaves,
cucumber, almonds, herbs and a drizzle of white
wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

Divide apricot glazed falafels, chermoula veggies and cucumber, mint and almond salad between plates. Serve with garlic dip.